<h1>New tiny home building code opening doors</h1>

<p><em>Plus: Democratic reps sue their own party, Xcel walks back massive rate hike request, Front Range inches closer to gas lawn equipment ban and more</em></p>

<!-- BYLINE -->
</mj-text><mj-table><tr style="border-top:1px solid #fcd232;border-bottom:1px solid #fcd232;text-align:left;"><td style="padding: 6px 3px;width:50px;"><img style="width:48px;height:48px;border:1px solid #fcd232;border-radius:50%; padding:0;" width="48px" height="48px" align="center" src="https://i0.wp.com/newspack-coloradosun.s3.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/eric-ig-portrait-square.jpg?resize=96,96"/></td><td style="padding: 6px 3px;width:50px;"><img style="width:48px;height:48px;border:1px solid #fcd232;border-radius:50%; padding:0;" width="48px" height="48px" align="center" src="https://i0.wp.com/newspack-coloradosun.s3.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/danikaworthington.jpeg?resize=96,96"/></td><td style="padding: 6px;"><strong>Eric Lubbers + Danika Worthington</strong><br /><a target="_blank"  href="https://coloradosun.com/author/eric-lubbers/?utm_source=newsletter&utm_source=The+Colorado+Sun+Newsletters&utm_campaign=SUNRISER_*|DATE:Ymd|*&utm_medium=email" target="_blank"><em><span style="font-size:12px;">CTO & Newsletter Wrangler</span></em></a> | <a target="_blank"  href="https://coloradosun.com/author/danika-worthington/?utm_source=newsletter&utm_source=The+Colorado+Sun+Newsletters&utm_campaign=SUNRISER_*|DATE:Ymd|*&utm_medium=email" target="_blank"><em><span style="font-size:12px;">Presentation Editor</span></em></a></td></tr></mj-table><mj-text>

<p>Good morning and happy 7/11 to all who celebrate. Now this is not a paid endorsement, but today does happen to be a free Slurpee day at any 7-Eleven â€” though if you have a more sophisticated palette (and access to a <a target="_blank"  href="https://www.google.com/maps/search/bahama+bucks+colorado/@39.7266977,-105.132969,11z/data=!3m1!4b1?entry=ttu">Bahama Buck&#8217;s</a>) you might want to opt for for a shaved ice, complete with Tajin and condensed milk. *<em>chef&#8217;s kiss*</em></p>

<p>But this year 7/11 giveth (free Slurpees) and taketh away (tolls on the I-70 express lanes). Now that Denver&#8217;s Big Dig to create the new I-70 configuration from downtown toward Aurora and the airport is complete, today is the day that tolls will begin on the express lanes (our pals <a target="_blank"  href="https://denverite.com/2023/07/07/i-70-express-lane-toll-start-date/">at Denverite have more info</a>, including how some residents of the Globeville and Elyria-Swansea neighborhoods can get subsidized passes for their vehicles).</p>

<p>So all in all, a pretty big day for a midsummer Tuesday. Whether you&#8217;re fighting brain freeze or traffic congestion, we&#8217;ve got the cure for what ails you: a bunch of interesting news from all over Colorado. (Don&#8217;t ask me how it will help; I&#8217;m a journalist, not a doctor/civil engineer.)</p>

<p>So let&#8217;s grab a long straw with a little spoon shape at the end and dig in, shall we?</p>

